frus:attachment.p:
An American expert, commissioned by Ambassador Ferguson and AID, has
                        recently surveyed the former Biafran area and believes that 80 per cent of
                        starch requirements can be met from present and prospective local crops;
                        Until the revival of normal commerce, however, she believes there will be
                        for some months a requirement for a large but decreasing amount of imported,
                        relief-supplied protein foods.
